HEADWORD: Pearlash
<hw>Pearl"ash`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Chem.)</fld>
<def>A white amorphous or granular substance which consists principally
of potassium carbonate, and has a strong alkaline reaction. It is
obtained by lixiviating wood ashes, and evaporating the lye, and has
been an important source of potassium compounds. It is used in making
soap, glass, etc.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

